      "widgets_values": [
        "\u2139\ufe0f High-Frequency Detail Masker (S-04)\n\nDefaults: kernel_type=laplacian, sensitivity=0.5, threshold_mode=relative_percentile.\n\n- kernel_type: 'laplacian' scale-invariant default; 'sobel' directional; 'fs_gaussian' reuses N-01 high-pass path.\n- sensitivity: fraction of pixels kept as detail. Higher = more pixels pass.\n- threshold_mode: 'relative_percentile' adapts per image (robust); 'absolute' normalizes by per-image max (deterministic).\n- Optional mask input: gate detail region (e.g., skin region from SAM).\n- Output is a MASK in [0, 1] — feed into MaskCompose / ImageBlend / SetLatentNoiseMask to preserve texture post-AI."
